Manage a persistent ELP daemon for fast turnaround

Usage: elp daemon [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  stop    Stop all running daemons
  status  Show daemon status for this project
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --project <PROJECT>  Path to directory with project, or to a JSON file [default: .]
      --as <PROFILE>       Rebar3 profile to pickup [default: test]
      --rebar              Run with rebar
  -h, --help               Print help

Global options:
      --log-file <LOG_FILE>  
      --erl <ERL>            
      --escript <ESCRIPT>    
      --no-log-buffering     
      --no-buck-generated    When using buck, do not invoke a build step for generated files
      --buck-quick-start     Use buck2 targets for first stage project loading
      --ifdef [<IFDEF>]      Deprecated: ifdef/ifndef condition evaluation is now enabled by
                             default. Pass `--ifdef false` to disable it [possible values: true,
                             false]
      --color <WHEN>         Use color in output [default: always] [possible values: always, never,
                             auto]
